{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Support student nurses with loan Forgiveness, fair pay & service recognition",
        "additional_details": "Starting a demanding nursing career with debt discourages students.\r\nRecognising 'continued years of service' for NHS staff who stop working for full-time healthcare study prevents financial and professional disadvantages for seeking career progression.\r\nUnpaid placements and rising living costs force students into extra jobs, impacting their studies and fitness to practice. Those without apprenticeships/sponsorship face financial hardship.\r\nReforming this will boost recruitment retention, and ensure a resilient, well-staffed workforce, ultimately strengthening the NHS.",
        "background": "I urge the Government to act now to support student nurses by implementing three key reforms:\r\n1) Forgive loans and restore free nursing education;\r\n2) Continued service recognition for NHS employees who stop work to complete a full-time nursing degree;\r\n3) An apprentice wage for placement hours",
